Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.ui

Class ActionConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eclipsesource.tabris.ui.ActionConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.eclipse.rap.rwt.Adaptable
    public class ActionConfiguration
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.eclipse.rap.rwt.Adaptable, java.io.Serializable

    Action objects will be instantiated by the framework. Therefore you need to be able to configure such an Action in a convenient way before it's actually created. This is the single purpose of a ActionConfiguration. It provides methods to define the visual role in a UI e.g. it's image or it's text.

    ActionConfiguration objects will be usually added to the UIConfiguration to have a global scope. Page actions needs to be added to a PageConfiguration.

    Since:
    0.11
    See Also:
    Action, UIConfiguration, PageConfiguration, Serialized Form
